column45: About 15-20 mins before I head out I suit up. Let my suit warm up to my body and in turn my body warm up to wearing the suit. I verify tire pressure while it’s on the warmers. Check to make sure my transponder is on my bike and start the bike to warm up. I normally race two bikes, but this past race I was down to one due to a mechanical issue. I review my notes on my track map that has my braking points, turn in markers, etc. try to visualize my route. Once I’ve done that for two las, my bike is up to temp and I shut it off to heat soak the motor and components. I put my ear plugs in. When it’s 2nd call, I text my wife to let her know I’m heading out and tell her I love her. I then put my helmet on and gloves. Final call I pull my warmers, hang them up and my pit mates pull my stands and send me out to battle
